  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "From which institute should I learn post production and lightning, sound camera etc for my YouTube channel in Delhi?",
  "response": "If you're looking for institutes in Delhi to learn post-production, lighting, sound, and camera techniques for your YouTube channel, here are some highly regarded options:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Film and Television Institute of India (FTII), Delhi Satellite Centre**\n   - Offers short-term courses in filmmaking, including post-production, cinematography, and sound design.\n   - Known for its industry-standard training and experienced faculty.\n   - Website: [ftii.ac.in](https://www.ftii.ac.in)\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Whistling Woods International (WWI), Delhi**\n   - Offers specialized courses in filmmaking, editing, sound design, and cinematography.\n   - Provides practical training with state-of-the-art equipment.\n   - Website: [whistlingwoods.net](https://www.whistlingwoods.net)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **ZIMA (Zee Institute of Media Arts), Delhi**\n   - Offers courses in video editing, cinematography, and sound design.\n   - Focuses on practical skills tailored for digital platforms like YouTube.\n   - Website: [zima.in](http://www.zima.in)\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Arena Animation, Delhi (Multiple Locations)**\n   - Offers courses in video editing, motion graphics, and sound design.\n   - Great for learning post-production software like Adobe Premiere Pro, After Effects, and DaVinci Resolve.\n   - Website: [arena-multimedia.in](https://www.arena-multimedia.in)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Digital Academy - The Film School, Delhi**\n   - Specializes in short-term courses in filmmaking, editing, and cinematography.\n   - Hands-on training with industry professionals.\n   - Website: [digitalacademyindia.com](http://www.digitalacademyindia.com)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Seamedu School of Pro-Expressionism, Delhi**\n   - Offers courses in sound design, cinematography, and post-production.\n   - Focuses on practical training for aspiring YouTubers and filmmakers.\n   - Website: [seamedu.com](https://www.seamedu.com)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **MasscoMedia, Delhi**\n   - Offers courses in video editing, sound, and cinematography.\n   - Affordable and tailored for beginners.\n   - Website: [masscomedia.com](https://www.masscomedia.com)\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Pearl Academy, Delhi**\n   - Offers courses in digital media production, including editing and sound design.\n   - Focuses on creative and technical skills for digital platforms.\n   - Website: [pearlacademy.com](https://www.pearlacademy.com)\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Maya Academy of Advanced Cinematics (MAAC), Delhi (Multiple Locations)**\n   - Offers courses in video editing, 3D animation, and VFX.\n   - Great for learning post-production techniques.\n   - Website: [maacindia.com](https://www.maacindia.com)\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Online Options**\n   - If you prefer flexibility, consider online platforms like **Udemy**, **Coursera**, or **Skillshare** for courses in editing, lighting, and sound design.\n\n---\n\n### Tips for Choosing the Right Institute:\n- **Check Curriculum:** Ensure the course covers the skills you need for your YouTube channel.\n- **Facilities:** Look for institutes with good equipment and practical training.\n- **Reviews:** Read student testimonials and reviews.\n- **Budget:** Compare fees and choose one that fits your budget.\n\nFor YouTube-specific content, focus on institutes or courses that emphasize **fast-paced editing**, **lighting for small setups**, and **sound recording for vlogs**.\n\nGood luck with your YouTube channel! \ud83c\udfa5\u2728",
  "temperature": 1.0,
